Biography:

Greensky Bluegrass is a five-piece American bluegrass band founded in Kalamazoo, Michigan in 2000. Bluegrass music has made a prominent resurgence with such "Newgrass" groups such as "The Devil Makes Three" and "Mumford and Sons" making splashes on the charts and attracting the attention of modern day music enthusiasts.

Recently, Greensky Bluegrass released their fifth studio album "If Sorrows Swim." Their signature sound is ever present and the album is sure to please any fan of Greensky, as well as any newcomers to the "Newgrass" movement.
